		"description": "<p>At 18th level, you can spend 1 hour in meditation to cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.866qabcoi5rezr16]{Astral Projection}, @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.jo2vztvypvhqxh5u]{Dream}, or @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.kv7igcz0o825new0]{Etherealness}. Each of these spells is slightly different when cast using this feature, as described below:</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Astral Projection.</em></strong> The spell requires no material components, but only affects you.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Dream.</em></strong> You are the messenger in the dream, and while you are influencing the dream you are completely detached from your body.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Etherealness</em></strong><em>.</em> When the spell ends, you reappear in the space you were in when you originally cast the spell.</p>\n<p>After using this feature, you cannot do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>",
